==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Necessitarian
<hw>Ne*ces`si*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the doctrine of philosophical necessity in regard to the
origin and existence of things, especially as applied to the actings or
choices of the will; -- opposed to <contr>libertarian</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necessitarian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Necessitarian
<hw>Ne*ces`si*ta"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who holds to the
doctrine of necessitarianism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necessitarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
